Changelog v2.1.7:
 - Device deduplication: nb_upsert_device() accepts primary_ip (8th arg);
   queries IPAM first, resolves owning interface/device, updates in-place
   instead of creating a duplicate when hostname improves on rescan
 - Smart rename: auto-generated names (device-A-B-C-D) upgraded to real
   hostnames; real names never downgraded back to auto-generated
 - sync_to_netbox(): passes $ip as 8th arg to nb_upsert_device()
 - merge_host_data(): scan_tier field (1=winrm 2=ssh 3=snmp 4=other)
   so heavier scans can detect and overwrite lighter previous records

Changelog v2.1.6:
 - Bug fix: missing # on section comment caused bash to execute ?? as command
 - Bug fix: save_config() wrote DEFAULT_SITE_NAME/TOKEN/PASS unquoted;
   spaces in values caused extra words to execute as commands on source
 - Bug fix: global NETBOX_API_URL retained localhost from v2.1.2 base;
   now initialised to "" with real value set after get_host_ip()
 - windows_credentials added to encrypted credential store
 - get_windows_creds_for(): per-device override then global list
 - Credential menu: Windows display, options 10/11, device override
   extended with windows_username/password/domain
 - nmap: ports 5985/5986 added; probe_winrm() parallel probe with nc
   port check, pywinrm/NTLM, lightweight PS inventory
 - merge_host_data(): WinRM overrides weaker sources; device_role from
   PS ProductType; winrm_nics passed through; winrm in discovery_methods
 - sync_to_netbox(): WinRM NIC loop with nb_ensure_mac_address()

Changelog v2.1.5:
 - Updated hostname to FQDN and modified clustername to ensure hostname only

Changelog v2.1.4:
 - Added full Hyper-V host hardware inventory sync:
   * CPU model -> cpu_model (custom field)
   * Logical processor count -> vcpus (custom field)
   * Physical RAM (MB + GB) -> memory_mb, memory_gb (custom fields)
   * OS version -> os_version (custom field)
 - Added host physical disk discovery:
   * Total disk capacity -> disk_total_gb (custom field)
   * Disk count -> disk_count (custom field)
   * Per-disk metadata -> disk_<n>_size_gb, disk_<n>_media, disk_<n>_interface
 - Automatic creation of all required custom fields for hosts:
   * Updated for NetBox 4.x: uses object_types=["dcim.device"]
   * Replaces deprecated content_types field
   * Fully idempotent GET-before-POST logic
 - Host NIC synchronization rewritten for NetBox 4.x:
   * Host NICs created under /dcim/interfaces/
   * MACs created as /dcim/mac-addresses/ objects
   * MACs assigned via assigned_object_type="dcim.interface"
   * Host interfaces now correctly set primary_mac_address=<mac_id>
     (fixes PRIMARY column showing X for host MACs)
 - Host IP synchronization fixed:
   * IPs created under /ipam/ip-addresses/ with shared=true
   * IPs assigned to host NICs via assigned_object_type="dcim.interface"
   * Host primary IPv4 set via device.primary_ip4
   * InterfaceIndex -> NetBox interface mapping added for accuracy
 - Cluster and device creation hardened:
   * Ensures manufacturer, device type, and role exist
   * Ensures cluster exists and is updated
   * Ensures device is created or patched idempotently
 - VM sync logic preserved and aligned with host behavior:
   * VM NICs use virtualization.vminterface
   * VM MACs created and assigned correctly
   * VM primary_mac_address set as before
   * VM primary IP assignment unchanged
   * VM virtual disk sync cleaned up and preserved
 - General NetBox 4.x compatibility improvements:
   * Removed deprecated interface mac_address field usage
   * All MAC operations now use /dcim/mac-addresses/
   * All interface primary MAC operations use primary_mac_address FK
   * All custom field creation updated to new schema

Changelog v2.1.3:
 - MAC address creation fixed for NetBox 4.x: mac_address field on
   dcim/interfaces and virtualization/interfaces is deprecated; MACs
   are now created as /dcim/mac-addresses/ objects with
   assigned_object_type + assigned_object_id, then set as
   primary_mac_address FK on the interface
 - Added nb_ensure_mac_address() helper used by nb_add_interface() and
   nb_add_vm_interface(); idempotent (GET-before-POST)
 - win_user / win_pass guaranteed initialised to "" (belt-and-suspenders
   fix; set -u cannot trigger even if device-override block is skipped)
 - Additional SNMP MIBs collected per host:
   * IF-MIB extended (1.3.6.1.2.1.31.1.1.1) -- ifAlias, ifHighSpeed
   * Entity MIB full table (1.3.6.1.2.1.47.1.1.1.1) -- model, serial,
     class (chassis/module/port/fan/psu); serial falls back to first
     chassis-class entity when .47.1.1.1.1.11.1 is absent
   * HOST-RESOURCES-MIB (1.3.6.1.2.1.25) -- processor load, storage
   * UCD-SNMP-MIB (1.3.6.1.4.1.2021) -- load averages, RAM (Linux)
   * EtherLike-MIB (1.3.6.1.2.1.10.7.2.1.19) -- duplex per interface
   * Power-Ethernet-MIB (1.3.6.1.2.1.105.1) -- PoE port status/class
   * Cisco CPU (1.3.6.1.4.1.9.9.109.1.1.1.1.8) / Memory pool
     (1.3.6.1.4.1.9.9.48.1.1.1.5/6) when available
 - Extra MIB data stored in snmp_details and surfaced in device comments

Changelog v2.1.2:
 - Fixed unbound variable errors under set -u: win_user, win_pass,
   ssh_user, ssh_pass, ssh_key all now initialised to "" in local decl
 - Replaced custom WinRM VM collector with full PowerShell template
   based on production-proven Hyper-V sync script; integrates:
   * MAC normalisation (UPPERCASE colon-separated for NetBox 4.x)
   * /dcim/mac-addresses/ object model with primary_mac_address FK
   * Virtual disk sync (virtualization/virtual-disks/)
   * Stale NIC cleanup; shared IP handling; primary IP assignment
   * IPAM prefix lookup for correct CIDR notation
   * Pre-flight connectivity checks against all used endpoints
   * TLS bypass for PS5 and PS7+ (dual Add-Type / PSDefaultParams)
 - import_hyperv_powershell(): looks up cluster-type and role IDs from
   NetBox at runtime; generates configured PS1; offers WinRM execution
   or file-save for manual run; sets $hyperVHost=$(get_host_ip) when running
   the script directly on the Hyper-V host via WinRM
 - Non-ASCII box-drawing characters removed from all comment lines

Changelog v2.1.1:
 - netbox-agent integration (https://pypi.org/project/netbox-agent/):
   production-stable Linux tool that registers servers/VMs into NetBox
   using dmidecode, lldpd, /sys/ parsing, ethtool, ipmitool, and lshw.
   Handles physical servers, blades, chassis, NICs, IPs, LLDP cables,
   inventory items (CPU/RAM/disk), VLAN auto-association, and hypervisor
   cluster/VM association. Tested on Hyper-V, VMware, VirtualBox, AWS, GCP.
 - install_deps: netbox-agent and pywinrm added to pip packages
 - generate_agent_config(): writes /etc/netbox_agent.yaml from current
   config (URL + token + sensible defaults including LLDP and inventory)
 - run_agent_local(): registers the discovery server itself via netbox-agent
 - deploy_agent_remote(): SSH to a discovered host, install netbox-agent,
   push config, and run --register in one step
 - deploy_agents_to_discovered(): batch-deploys to all Linux hosts in the
   latest results file (skips Windows/firewall/non-SSH hosts)
 - import_hyperv_windows(): WinRM/NTLM path for Windows Hyper-V hosts;
   uses pywinrm + PowerShell to enumerate VMs; imports to NetBox
   virtualization/clusters and virtualization/virtual-machines API
 - NetBox API helpers added: nb_get_or_create_cluster_type(),
   nb_get_or_create_cluster(), nb_upsert_vm(), nb_add_vm_interface()
 - New menu: menu_import() with options for all import paths
 - Main menu: option 9 "Import / Agent Deployment"

Changelog v2.1.0:
 - REAL_USER tracking: captures sudo caller for docker group management
 - ensure_docker_group(): creates docker group and adds REAL_USER; called
   from install_deps() so the deploying user can run docker without sudo
 - Multi-subnet discovery: input now accepts comma-separated CIDRs,
   space-separated CIDRs, or a file path containing one target per line
 - Subnet file format: supports CIDR ranges and bare IPs; lines starting
   with # are treated as comments; leading/trailing whitespace stripped;
   inline comments (# after value) supported
 - Host scan file (Option 3): same improvements -- CIDR expansion,
   comment lines, whitespace stripping, inline comments
 - parse_targets(): new helper that normalises any mix of CIDRs/IPs/files
   into a clean target list used by all discovery entry points
 - discover_targets(): loops over parsed targets, calls discover_live_hosts
   per target, then deduplicates the combined result before Phase 2
 - Django shell token creation aligned with netbox-docker super_user.py:
   uses get_or_create for idempotency, only sets password when creating new
   user, no key= passed to Token.objects.create() so NetBox generates
   its own native-format key (required for NetBox 4.5+ varchar(12) field)

Changelog v2.0.9:
 - Serial sanitization: SNMP error strings (e.g. "No Such Object...",
   "iso.3.6.1...") are cleared; serial limited to 50 chars
 - Device-type slug collision: on POST failure, falls back to slug search
   so re-runs find the existing type rather than failing silently
 - Model name truncated to 64 chars before slugifying to avoid slug drift
 - nb_api: removed -f flag from curl; API error responses now captured
 - nb_upsert_device: logs full API error body on POST failure
 - IP filtering: 0.0.0.0, 127.x, 169.254.x skipped in interface sync
 - probe_snmp: SNMP error strings cleared from chassis_serial field

Changelog v2.0.8:
 - Fixed "value too long for type character varying(12)" on deploy.
   NetBox v4.5 changed Token.key format; passing a pre-generated hex key
   fails. Removed SUPERUSER_API_TOKEN/KEY from override yml. Django shell
   now uses Token.objects.create(user=u) with NO key= argument.

